snippet.textDisplay:
You say "Do you know how crazy it is to stun your opponent by roundhouse kicking them and landing with only your toes"
I don't find it crazy at all. The toes are traveling much faster than anything else. It's the kinetic chain. Like cracking a whip. For example, when you pitch a baseball your fingers are the fastest moving. The end of a lever will ALWAYS carry the most energy. If you want to understand this just have someone kick you with the toes and end of the foot. It can be like a strong punch from a skilled kicker. So it's really not all that crazy once you understand kinetic energy and levers.
